description.p:
The present invention relates to a method to control an on board unit (OBU) within a communication zone of a road side unit (RSU), said OBU can be set into an active mode and a sleep mode, wherein the OBU is set into;

said sleep mode when said OBU receives a release command from said RSU, and the electronics of said OBU thereby is shut down, such that no or a minimum of power is consumed, and

said active mode when said OBU is entering said communication zone, whereby a communication unit of said OBU thereby is powered such that the OBU can communicate with said RSU, wherein said OBU can be set into a tracking mode by said RSU, whereby in said tracking mode at least said communication unit is shut down and a timer is activated in said OBU, such that said OBU can restart said communication unit within a specified time limit from it is shut down.
